cs.DC, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.NE 

This paper is about developing machine learning techniques to generate efficient scheduling policies for data processing jobs on distributed compute clusters. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also extensively uses reinforcement learning (RL) and neural networks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with designing scalable RL models and inventing RL training methods, which could place it in cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
